			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How do people twist more than 3 songs?<a name="73091"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 05 2:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Most of our songs last 3 ticks, and you can keep three of them up in a twist without having anything drop.  Some people try and twist four, which tends to result in at least one song dropping at all times.
<br />

<br />
There are some times when it does not matter if a song drops.  The main one being our Chants.  They still do full damage, so stacking four or more works all right.  There has been some discussion as to how effective more than four Chants is, with at least some math to suggest that more than four ends up doing slightly *less* dps.  The issue is not all that clear cut.
<br />

<br />
There are some few songs which last longer than 3 ticks.  Adding those to a twist can allow you to have more than three songs up, with only the occasional song dropping.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
