				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How do people twist more than 3 songs?<a name="73094"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 05 3:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Like Elfvus, I just stop a song just before the casting bar reaches the end and start the next one. I can keep 4 up with no problems, barring the occasional stop-start-stop bug and multiple missed notes. It has a lot to do with your connection and machine too. It's a lot easier to twist 4 with my newer 3.2 g, 1g ram, PCI-e machine on cable then it was on my old 850m P3, 512 ram, PCI (old) machine running with AOL.
<br />

<br />
Also, my understanding is that /melody is run server side, so you should get consistent results for a 4 song twist using that. I only use /melody for soloing though...</span></td>
