				<td colspan="2"><span>3 is the usual. I would do 4 but I get hammered by the stop/start/stop bug.  5 is not reliable, you WILL drop a song every time, its just plain maths.
<br />

<br />
Of course adding songs with &gt; 12 sec duration changes that, so for instance you can land Assonance and then go to a 4 dot twist, giving you 5 songs for up to a minute.
<br />

<br />
But for the most part 4 is the limit and even then the bug means it's not practical (for me).
<br />

<br />
You can play stupid games to see how many songs you can get going. e.g.
<br />

<br />
Selo's
<br />
Sustenance
<br />
Assonance
<br />
Amp
<br />
4 normal duration songs.
<br />

<br />
Or something along those lines...
<br />

<br />
So you can get big numbers, but not of any practical value.
<br />

<br />
3 is the way to go for reliability and relaxation
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
