				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How do people twist more than 3 songs?<a name="73156"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 12 05 12:38 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As to the multiple chant thing, it's more trouble than it's worth to try and dig back through the posts and find where I read about it.
<br />

<br />
As best I remember it went like this:
<br />

<br />
You can throw all the chants you want at a mob, but after four, they almost certainly will be wearing off before you can reapply them.  This would not matter except for one little thing.  Resists.  If a mob resists a chant, you get no damage at all for it that round.
<br />

<br />
The chants have a debuff component.  If the chant has not worn off when you go to re-sing it, the odds are less that the mob will resist it.
<br />

<br />
Chants also have a fizzle mod.  You are more likely to miss notes when doing them than with most songs, because Sony likes it that way.  This makes it even harder to keep a set of them up.
<br />

<br />
I seem to remember someone who was into parsing who had data to back up the idea that four chants was good, more than that resulted in a higher rate of resists, and an over all drop in dps.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
