			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In response to the cast bar question: I'm not 100% on that information, it could be that I DECIDE to hit the button before the cast bar clears, and then I hit it AS its disappearing.  The difference we are talking about is minimal, but I tend to be able to keep 4 up most of the time.  Basically, what I do is wait until the cast bar is 1/3-1/4 of the way through the last bubble, and then double-press the next button.  I also tend not to use macros (I don't raid too much, so that may change) because I don't like the idea of a delay on them--even though it is likely about the same delay that I have, and more consistent.  I hope it makes sense to wait almost until the cast bar is gone before starting your next twist...but not all the way, I might have to go try it sometime when I am awake and alert and that sorta stuff.  Also, I noticed that a few songs (the only ones I found are Battlecry of the Vah Shir, Magical Monologue, Katta's Song of Sword Dancing, and the DS Psalms (I think) that claim to be the normal 3-tic timer seem to actually be a on a four tic timer.  There could be some more, but I'm only 57 ATM, so I dunno.  Sorry, I'm tired so I'm blathering on like a fool...</span></td>
